1201
01:18:19,192 --> 01:18:21,516
...as defense exhibit B, C, D, E and F.

1202
01:18:21,673 --> 01:18:24,717
How much light comes in
with no window when the door is closed?

1203
01:18:24,873 --> 01:18:28,039
- Not much.
- How long was Henri held in such a cell?

1204
01:18:28,193 --> 01:18:29,394
I don't know exactly.

1205
01:18:29,554 --> 01:18:32,916
Three years and two months.
I have the records here, if you'd like to see.

1206
01:18:33,075 --> 01:18:35,203
- That sounds right.
- Three years and two months.

1207
01:18:35,355 --> 01:18:38,880
In that time, how often was Henri Young
allowed outside for exercise?

1208
01:18:39,035 --> 01:18:43,358
Mr. Stamphill, I do not believe that
the exercise time of an inmate is relevant.

1209
01:18:43,517 --> 01:18:45,001
Well, I do. Answer the question.

1210
01:18:45,157 --> 01:18:46,161
Objection.

1211
01:18:46,317 --> 01:18:48,685
Objection overruled.
- Henri Young tried to escape.

1212
01:18:48,838 --> 01:18:52,079
Now, when a criminal escapes from prison,
he doesn't go job-hunting.

1213
01:18:52,238 --> 01:18:55,807
He robs somebody or kills somebody.
We do all we can to discourage escape.

1214
01:18:55,959 --> 01:18:59,888
In three years and two months, how often
was Henri allowed outside for exercise?

1215
01:19:00,039 --> 01:19:03,368
- I do not believe men sentenced-
- Answer the question I'm asking.

1216
01:19:03,520 --> 01:19:06,009
How often was he allowed outside
for exercise?

1217
01:19:06,161 --> 01:19:07,689
Objection. Badgering the witness.

1218
01:19:07,841 --> 01:19:09,042
Objection overruled.

1219
01:19:09,202 --> 01:19:11,483
Mr. Glenn, you will answer that question.

1220
01:19:12,802 --> 01:19:14,886
Young man, I do not recall.

1221
01:19:15,043 --> 01:19:16,364
Heh. You don't know?

1222
01:19:16,523 --> 01:19:19,372
Surely a half hour a year
isn't too difficult to recall, now, is it?

1223
01:19:19,523 --> 01:19:22,644
Mr. Stamphill, there is no place
in my courtroom for sarcasm.

1224
01:19:22,804 --> 01:19:25,969
Sorry, Your Honor. Mr. Glenn,
I have here a list with 32 names on it.

1225
01:19:26,125 --> 01:19:30,086
Now, these are all men who were prisoners
at Alcatraz during your tenure. Correct?

1226
01:19:30,245 --> 01:19:32,210
I can't remember the name
of every prisoner.

1227
01:19:32,366 --> 01:19:34,407
I have committal papers
with your signature...

1228
01:19:34,567 --> 01:19:36,171
...as well as the late Dr. Wendell Kiley.

1229
01:19:36,327 --> 01:19:38,848
We'd like this to be marked
defense exhibit G.

1230
01:19:39,007 --> 01:19:43,013
All of these men were taken off Alcatraz
in straitjackets and placed in institutions.

1231
01:19:43,168 --> 01:19:46,213
- Is that correct?
- Objection. The question is immaterial.

1232
01:19:46,369 --> 01:19:50,811
Immaterial? Your Honor, I'm saying in lay
terms that Alcatraz drives people insane.

1233
01:19:50,969 --> 01:19:52,737
It has already done so in 32 instances.

1234
01:19:52,890 --> 01:19:55,694
If not true, the witness ought to have
the opportunity to say so.

1235
01:19:55,850 --> 01:19:57,891
If it is true, it is most material...

1236
01:19:58,050 --> 01:20:00,812
and the jury ought to be privy
to that knowledge.

1237
01:20:00,971 --> 01:20:03,416
- Objection overruled.
- Thank you.

1238
01:20:03,572 --> 01:20:08,777
Now, is it not true that these men
were taken off Alcatraz in straightjackets...

1239
01:20:08,933 --> 01:20:13,134
...and placed in mental institutions and you
and Dr. Wendell Kiley signed the papers?

1240
01:20:13,293 --> 01:20:16,622
- True.
- Is it not also true that of these 32 men...

1241
01:20:16,774 --> 01:20:19,940
...28 of them had never before set foot
inside a mental institution?

1242
01:20:20,095 --> 01:20:22,660
- Ha-ha-ha. I don't know.
- I have their records if you'd like to see.

1243
01:20:22,815 --> 01:20:24,616
- Well, I'll take your word for it.
- Okay.

1244
01:20:24,776 --> 01:20:27,538
Here are men who came to Alcatraz
legally sane...

1245
01:20:27,696 --> 01:20:31,221
...were subjected to the conditions
of Alcatraz, then deemed to be insane.

1246
01:20:31,376 --> 01:20:33,297
- Is that correct?
- Yes, but you can't say...

1247
01:20:33,457 --> 01:20:35,062
...that one causes the other.

1248
01:20:35,217 --> 01:20:38,699
Well, insanity's not a virus, is it?
It's not something we're all going to catch.

1249
01:20:38,858 --> 01:20:41,379
Objection, Your Honor.
The witness is not a psychiatrist.

1250
01:20:41,538 --> 01:20:42,947
Objection sustained.

1251
01:20:43,259 --> 01:20:47,548
Mr. Stamphill, confine your questions
to areas of Mr. Glenn's expertise.

1252
01:20:47,700 --> 01:20:51,225
Very well. Mr. Glenn's expertise.
Have you ever beaten a prisoner?

1253
01:20:51,381 --> 01:20:52,582
No, that would be illegal.

1254
01:20:52,741 --> 01:20:54,182
- Not even when provoked?
- No.

1255
01:20:54,341 --> 01:20:57,507
You've never hit, kicked,
used a blackjack or straight razor?

1256
01:20:57,662 --> 01:21:00,150
You've never punched a prisoner
in your entire career?

1257
01:21:00,303 --> 01:21:02,191
- Objection, Your Honor.
- Sustained.

1258
01:21:02,343 --> 01:21:04,263
Confine yourself
to one question at a time.

1259
01:21:04,424 --> 01:21:08,625
Is it not true that you ordered two guards
to throw Henri down a steel flight of stairs?

1260
01:21:08,784 --> 01:21:10,913
That you smashed his face
with a blackjack?

1261
01:21:11,064 --> 01:21:14,513
That you took a straight razor, sliced open
his ankle, hobbling him for life?

1262
01:21:14,665 --> 01:21:16,193
That's the truth, isn't it?

1263
01:21:16,346 --> 01:21:18,834
- Objection.
- The witness has already testified...

1264
01:21:18,986 --> 01:21:20,666
...he didn't beat any prisoners.

1265
01:21:20,826 --> 01:21:24,187
Are you aware that, in a federal court
system, perjury is a crime?

1266
01:21:24,347 --> 01:21:26,114
You could spend time in prison.

1267
01:21:26,267 --> 01:21:28,187
I would remind you, young man...

1268
01:21:28,347 --> 01:21:30,268
...Henri Young is the one on trial here,
not me.

1269
01:21:30,428 --> 01:21:33,277
I am a public servant.
I am not the bad guy.

1270
01:21:33,428 --> 01:21:38,678
I will not be treated the same way as
this lying, murdering, two-time loser!

1271
01:21:38,830 --> 01:21:40,151
Silence, Mr. Glenn.

1272
01:21:40,310 --> 01:21:45,156
Mr. Stamphill, you are perilously close
to contempt of this court.

1273
01:21:45,310 --> 01:21:48,955
You will proceed with caution.
Is that understood?

1274
01:21:50,592 --> 01:21:52,512
Temper, temper.

1275
01:21:55,192 --> 01:21:57,277
Well, would you care to withdraw
any testimony?

1276
01:21:57,433 --> 01:22:01,122
You wouldn't want somebody to come along
and testify to the contrary, would you?

1277
01:22:01,434 --> 01:22:06,477
No. I would not withdraw any testimony,
no matter what Henri Young has told you.

1278
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:10,160
I'm not talking about Henri Young.
Who would believe him?

1279
01:22:11,036 --> 01:22:13,676
Mr. Simpson, did you ever
beat this man, Henri Young?

1280
01:22:13,836 --> 01:22:15,800
Objection, Your Honor.
This has no bearing.

1281
01:22:15,957 --> 01:22:19,242
No bearing? Your Honor, beatings have
a bearing on a man's state of mind.

1282
01:22:19,397 --> 01:22:21,285
Three years of darkness has a bearing.

1283
01:22:21,437 --> 01:22:23,358
Do we need to be psychologists
to know that?

1284
01:22:23,518 --> 01:22:25,559
You know that, Your Honor.
I know you do.

1285
01:22:25,718 --> 01:22:28,403
- Objection overruled.
- Thank you, Your Honor.

1286
01:22:28,559 --> 01:22:29,563
Mr. Simpson...

1287
01:22:29,719 --> 01:22:31,881
...did you ever beat Henri Young
with a blackjack?

1288
01:22:32,040 --> 01:22:33,044
Yes.

1289
01:22:33,199 --> 01:22:35,884
Did you ever throw Henri Young
down a steel?ight of stairs?

1290
01:22:36,041 --> 01:22:38,082
- I did.
- You were ordered to do this?

1291
01:22:38,241 --> 01:22:40,282
- Yes.
- Tell us the name of the man...

1292
01:22:40,442 --> 01:22:43,126
...who was your superior,
who ordered you to do these things.

1293
01:22:43,282 --> 01:22:44,690
- Mr. Glenn.
- Mr. Glenn.

1294
01:22:44,842 --> 01:22:47,963
- You never went to Warden Humson?
- No, sir.

1295
01:22:48,123 --> 01:22:51,244
Thank you very much. I won't ask
where you got your bruises. I know.

1296
01:22:51,404 --> 01:22:52,528
Your witness.

1297
01:22:52,683 --> 01:22:55,248
The prosecution would like to mark
for identification...

1298
01:22:55,404 --> 01:22:58,012
...the employment records
of Mr. Derek Simpson.

1299
01:22:58,164 --> 01:23:03,010
Do you recall, Mr. Simpson,
being suspended on November 4th, 1936...

1300
01:23:03,166 --> 01:23:06,407
...and again on July 6th, 1937?

1301
01:23:06,566 --> 01:23:08,607
- Yeah.
- Speak up, Mr. Simpson.

1302
01:23:09,487 --> 01:23:10,611
Yes.

1303
01:23:10,766 --> 01:23:15,612
Is it not a fact you were fired from your job
as a guard because you are a drunk?

1304
01:23:15,768 --> 01:23:17,492
- Objection.
- That's not true.

1305
01:23:17,648 --> 01:23:18,772
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1306
01:23:18,928 --> 01:23:21,930
And that Mr. Glenn would not tolerate this
in a federal prison.

1307
01:23:22,089 --> 01:23:24,610
Isn't it true, Mr. Simpson,
having cost you your job...

1308
01:23:24,769 --> 01:23:27,574
...you would say just about anything
to get even with Mr. Glenn?

1309
01:23:28,490 --> 01:23:29,811
The jury will disregard.

1310
01:23:29,970 --> 01:23:32,371
...Mr. Simpson's testimony.

1311
01:23:32,931 --> 01:23:37,013
Good afternoon. Mr. Stamphill,
Mr. Stamphill, is everything all right?

1312
01:23:46,973 --> 01:23:48,861
You son of a bitch.
- What happened?

1313
01:23:49,014 --> 01:23:50,859
You know what happened. You set me up.

1314
01:23:51,014 --> 01:23:54,016
- What are you talking about?
- You took Simpson's picture.

1315
01:23:54,175 --> 01:23:56,980
They never would have known to tear
Simpson down if you hadn't told them.

1316
01:23:57,135 --> 01:23:59,220
Are you gonna hit me now, James?

1317
01:23:59,376 --> 01:24:00,620
Go ahead.

1318
01:24:00,776 --> 01:24:03,898
It's about time you grew up
and were a man.

1319
01:24:08,257 --> 01:24:09,262
You're my brother.

1320
01:24:10,578 --> 01:24:14,462
- You had me beaten up.
- James, that was not supposed to happen.

1321
01:24:14,619 --> 01:24:17,020
Only Simpson. You walked in,
it was bad timing.

1322
01:24:17,179 --> 01:24:19,143
Bad timing?

1323
01:24:21,620 --> 01:24:23,028
I'm putting Humson on the stand.

1324
01:24:23,181 --> 01:24:26,106
Why, James?
Humson doesn't know anything!

1325
01:24:26,741 --> 01:24:30,703
Man runs three prisons. He has to know
something. Unless he's never there.

1326
01:24:35,063 --> 01:24:37,027
Son of a bitch.

1327
01:24:40,623 --> 01:24:43,472
He was never there. Never there.

1328
01:24:43,624 --> 01:24:45,032
You never saw him?

1329
01:24:45,184 --> 01:24:48,993
No. You'd hear about
him visiting, but I never saw him.

1330
01:24:50,026 --> 01:24:52,666
Now, your own brother did that to you?
Your brother did that to you?

1331
01:24:52,826 --> 01:24:55,707
Yeah.
- Jesus, rich people are weird.

1332
01:24:55,866 --> 01:24:57,350
Hey, he)'-

1333
01:24:57,507 --> 01:25:01,708
You hear DiMaggio broke Keeler's record?
Forty-five straight games.

1334
01:25:01,867 --> 01:25:03,712
Wouldn't it be great if he never stopped?

1335
01:25:03,868 --> 01:25:07,109
Dock records show when he was here.
Every trip to Alcatraz is recorded.

1336
01:25:07,269 --> 01:25:09,310
- I had to sign in that time I went.
- Hey, Jim.

1337
01:25:09,469 --> 01:25:11,117
- What?
- We friends, huh?

1338
01:25:11,269 --> 01:25:12,394
Yeah, sure.

1339
01:25:12,550 --> 01:25:15,911
Is it over? I mean, you know? Is that all?

1340
01:25:16,070 --> 01:25:18,919
Nothing more you're gonna do
with the trial, I mean?

1341
01:25:19,071 --> 01:25:21,832
- Thought you didn't care.
- No, I don't care. I don't care.

1342
01:25:21,992 --> 01:25:25,713
It's just, you know, long as you got shit
to throw at them, we can keep talking.

1343
01:25:25,872 --> 01:25:27,596
But when it's over, it's over, huh?

1344
01:25:27,753 --> 01:25:30,634
I'm not here to keep you entertained
until the executioner comes.

1345
01:25:30,793 --> 01:25:32,561
- This trial isn't just a game.
- Hey, Jim.

1346
01:25:32,714 --> 01:25:34,078
What?

1347
01:25:37,674 --> 01:25:41,439
If I was on the outside- I mean, you know,
if there was, like, a good fairy...

1348
01:25:41,595 --> 01:25:44,956
...and she waved a wand
and I was on the outside...

1349
01:25:45,116 --> 01:25:47,636
...you and me, would we be friends then?

1350
01:25:47,797 --> 01:25:51,486
- Yes.
- No, no, no, we wouldn't.

1351
01:25:51,637 --> 01:25:54,803
You wouldn't have nothing to do with me.
You know it.

1352
01:25:54,957 --> 01:25:57,926
What I can't figure out is why, you know.

1353
01:25:58,078 --> 01:26:02,127
I mean, we both ain't got nobody else
and we're the same age, sort of.

1354
01:26:02,279 --> 01:26:05,204
And if I'd have lived in your house...

1355
01:26:05,360 --> 01:26:09,125
...and they'd have switched us
when we was babies...

1356
01:26:09,280 --> 01:26:11,768
...I could have been just like you.

1357
01:26:11,921 --> 01:26:13,602
If they stuck you down in the hole...

1358
01:26:15,721 --> 01:26:17,926
...you could be sitting here just like me...

1359
01:26:18,082 --> 01:26:22,644
...asking how come we couldn't be friends
on the outside. You ever steal 5 bucks?

1360
01:26:25,963 --> 01:26:31,485
Once, when I was a kid,
from my brother's wallet.

1361
01:26:32,964 --> 01:26:34,492
What happened?

1362
01:26:36,125 --> 01:26:39,366
He told me not to do it again.

1363
01:26:41,486 --> 01:26:44,771
Why'd they put me in that hole
for three years?

1364
01:26:45,727 --> 01:26:48,335
I could have been just like you.

1365
01:26:50,488 --> 01:26:53,009
I'd just like to ask them, you know.

1366
01:27:06,771 --> 01:27:08,539
Raise your right hand.

1367
01:27:09,492 --> 01:27:13,137
Do you swear to tell the whole truth and
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

1368
01:27:13,292 --> 01:27:14,580
So help me God.

1369
01:27:14,973 --> 01:27:16,817
You may be seated.

1370
01:27:21,373 --> 01:27:25,379
Warden Humson, in a book you wrote,
you refer to the convicts as your children.

1371
01:27:25,695 --> 01:27:29,536
That you liken your job to that of a parent,
providing for their physical needs...

1372
01:27:29,696 --> 01:27:31,463
...and molding their character.

1373
01:27:31,616 --> 01:27:33,820
Mm-hm. Yes, I wrote that.

1374
01:27:33,977 --> 01:27:38,823
I have a record of a prisoner named Johnson
who did 500 days in the lower cells.

1375
01:27:38,977 --> 01:27:41,061
The hole, the dungeon.

1376
01:27:41,218 --> 01:27:45,780
This was a 10-year period for such offenses
as not finishing all the food on his plate...

1377
01:27:45,938 --> 01:27:49,583
...having an extra pair of socks
in his cell, keeping an untidy cell.

1378
01:27:50,179 --> 01:27:54,185
Um, smuggling food from the dining room,
crumbs, in fact, to a pet lizard.

1379
01:27:54,340 --> 01:27:56,905
Is this what you mean
when you say "molding character"?

1380
01:27:57,060 --> 01:28:00,182
No, no, no. You're twisting things here.

1381
01:28:00,341 --> 01:28:05,143
The isolation cells were simply a tool
of a temporary nature...

1382
01:28:05,302 --> 01:28:09,547
...for extreme cases
within the general population.

1383
01:28:09,703 --> 01:28:14,308
Moreover, you make it sound like
the prisoner did 1500 days at one stretch...

1384
01:28:14,463 --> 01:28:16,111
...for one infraction.

1385
01:28:16,264 --> 01:28:18,468
That's not true.

1386
01:28:18,624 --> 01:28:24,267
No. Prisoners were held
for 19 days at a time.

1387
01:28:24,426 --> 01:28:25,954
- That's all.
- That's all.

1388
01:28:27,106 --> 01:28:30,991
Perhaps you can tell me why Henri Young
did over 1000 days in the dungeon?

1389
01:28:31,147 --> 01:28:33,755
Not 19 days, but 1000 days...

1390
01:28:33,908 --> 01:28:37,269
...in total darkness with only 30 minutes
of daylight a year.

1391
01:28:37,428 --> 01:28:39,229
Yes. But he tried to escape.

1392
01:28:39,389 --> 01:28:43,634
You can't compare his offense with that of
a man who smuggled food to a lizard.

1393
01:28:43,790 --> 01:28:46,834
Now, this was the first time a
sentence of three years had been imposed?

1394
01:28:46,990 --> 01:28:48,114
It wasn't a sentence.

1395
01:28:48,270 --> 01:28:51,195
It was an administrative decision
to place him there, uh...

1396
01:28:51,350 --> 01:28:54,112
...for an undetermined amount of time.

1397
01:28:54,271 --> 01:28:57,916
Why not a time limit? Doesn't that seem
a little bit inhumane? No time limit.

1398
01:28:58,071 --> 01:28:59,959
Put simply, no.

1399
01:29:00,952 --> 01:29:04,434
While we strive to prevent crime...

1400
01:29:04,593 --> 01:29:07,562
...what shall we do with the man
who has committed it, hm?

1401
01:29:07,714 --> 01:29:10,715
We aim to make him his better self.

1402
01:29:10,874 --> 01:29:12,282
His better self.

1403
01:29:12,875 --> 01:29:15,877
Well, I'm sure that Henri Young thanks you
for his better self.

1404
01:29:16,036 --> 01:29:19,965
It's a fact you simply put Henri Young
in that dungeon and forgot all about him.

1405
01:29:20,436 --> 01:29:21,724
Washed your hands of him.

1406
01:29:21,876 --> 01:29:25,282
Henri wanted me to ask you why.
Why would you do that, sir? Why?

1407
01:29:25,437 --> 01:29:28,002
- Objection, Your Honor.
- That's not true.

1408
01:29:28,157 --> 01:29:30,722
I withdraw the question.
I apologize to the jury-

1409
01:29:30,878 --> 01:29:33,802
It's not necessary that you apologize.

1410
01:29:33,959 --> 01:29:36,928
Actually, Your Honor, it is.
You see, I made a mistake.

1411
01:29:37,079 --> 01:29:40,168
Warden Humson couldn't simply
have washed his hands of Henri Young.

1412
01:29:40,319 --> 01:29:41,324
He couldn't have.

1413
01:29:41,480 --> 01:29:44,121
Because he had absolutely no idea
he was there.

1414
01:29:44,281 --> 01:29:46,290
Isn't that true, warden?
You are never there.

1415
01:29:46,441 --> 01:29:49,246
And you permit Glenn to run that prison
any way he sees fit.

1416
01:29:49,401 --> 01:29:53,003
I am there as much as I need to be.
I run three penal institutions.

1417
01:29:53,402 --> 01:29:57,287
It's impossible to know every detail
of every inmate.

1418
01:29:57,443 --> 01:29:59,244
I have the port authority records...

1419
01:29:59,403 --> 01:30:02,208
...which you signed
every time you went to Alcatraz.

1420
01:30:02,364 --> 01:30:06,370
You went seven times in '38,
five in '39, 10 in '40...

1421
01:30:06,524 --> 01:30:10,409
...and only twice so far this year. Twenty-four
day trips in three and a half years...

1422
01:30:10,566 --> 01:30:13,894
...while Henri Young was in that dungeon
over 1000 days.

1423
01:30:14,047 --> 01:30:16,328
Twenty-four out of 1000 days.

1424
01:30:16,487 --> 01:30:18,528
That's as much as you needed
to be there?

1425
01:30:18,687 --> 01:30:21,569
You knew nothing about a man
who was left to die in a dungeon...

1426
01:30:21,728 --> 01:30:24,173
...for three and a half years, did you?
Absolutely nothing.

1427
01:30:24,328 --> 01:30:28,138
In fact, you have never even met
Henri Young, have you?

1428
01:30:28,289 --> 01:30:32,131
Right now, in fact, is the first time
you have ever seen this man. Look at him.

1429
01:30:32,609 --> 01:30:34,934
That's him there. That's Henri Young.
Right there.

1430
01:30:35,090 --> 01:30:36,890
- He tried to escape.
- He tried to escape.

1431
01:30:37,051 --> 01:30:39,932
But the fact, the cold, brutal fact,
Warden Humson...

1432
01:30:40,091 --> 01:30:43,693
...is that this man, who had never,
never before in his entire life...

1433
01:30:43,851 --> 01:30:46,733
...harmed or attempted to harm
another human being, never...

1434
01:30:46,892 --> 01:30:49,097
...was now a murderer.
That is a fact, is it not?

1435
01:30:49,253 --> 01:30:51,577
- Yes. No, he tried to escape.
- It is equally a fact-

1436
01:30:51,733 --> 01:30:54,298
You can't let them get away with this.

1437
01:30:54,454 --> 01:30:56,615
If we let them get away with this,
where would we be?

1438
01:30:56,774 --> 01:31:00,736
- What? Should we let murderers roam free?
- Henri Young was not a murderer.

1439
01:31:00,895 --> 01:31:04,016
Henri Young was not a murderer
until Alcatraz got a hold of him.

1440
01:31:04,175 --> 01:31:08,585
Now, the prison runs under your guidelines,
so you created the murderer, didn't you?

1441
01:31:08,737 --> 01:31:10,384
Didn't you?

1442
01:31:11,337 --> 01:31:14,546
He tried to escape.

1443
01:31:15,657 --> 01:31:18,626
That's the thing, you see.

1444
01:31:23,419 --> 01:31:24,424
Mr. Stamphill...

1445
01:31:24,579 --> 01:31:27,187
...do you have any further questions
for this witness?

1446
01:31:28,180 --> 01:31:31,541
- No, Your Honor.
- The witness may step down.

1447
01:31:31,700 --> 01:31:33,425
But he tried to escape.

1448
01:31:34,221 --> 01:31:36,350
I'd been trained all my life for that day.

1449
01:31:36,501 --> 01:31:39,022
Control the witness, go for the kill.

1450
01:31:39,182 --> 01:31:41,703
Win, victory.

1451
01:31:41,862 --> 01:31:43,750
School prepared me well

1452
01:31:43,904 --> 01:31:46,424
My brother, he had prepared me well.

1453
01:31:46,703 --> 01:31:49,825
Years later, he and I would reconcile.

1454
01:31:50,304 --> 01:31:52,553
Family's family, you know.

1455
01:31:53,505 --> 01:31:58,187
Mary congratulated me,
but we'd already begun to drift apart.

1456
01:31:59,026 --> 01:32:02,791
When you only try to win,
you sometimes lose sight of the goal...

1457
01:32:03,266 --> 01:32:04,914
...which should have always
remained Henri.

1458
01:32:16,429 --> 01:32:18,590
No way they're gonna
send you to the gas chamber.

1459
01:32:18,749 --> 01:32:20,953
Most is second-degree murder.
Maybe manslaughter.

1460
01:32:21,110 --> 01:32:23,838
Ten years, if you get clemency,
and you'll walk.

1461
01:32:23,990 --> 01:32:27,396
- You'll have your whole life in front of you.
- Monday morning...

1462
01:32:27,551 --> 01:32:31,153
...I want you to get up to that judge
and tell him there's been a change of plan.

1463
01:32:31,312 --> 01:32:34,433
I want you to get up there
and change my plea to guilty.

1464
01:32:35,352 --> 01:32:38,201
- That's a joke, right?
- Not to me, it's not.

1465
01:32:38,354 --> 01:32:39,882
I'm not doing it.

1466
01:32:40,033 --> 01:32:43,678
What the hell have I been doing here?
Why have I been wasting my time?

1467
01:32:43,835 --> 01:32:46,039
I never thought we'd win.

1468
01:32:46,194 --> 01:32:48,039
I thought you wanted to fight.

1469
01:32:48,195 --> 01:32:51,197
I just wanted a friend.

1470
01:32:51,596 --> 01:32:55,044
- Henri, I am your friend.
- No, you're not. No, you're not.

1471
01:32:55,197 --> 01:32:57,281
It's always about you.
It's never about me.

1472
01:32:57,436 --> 01:32:59,237
You don't understand.

1473
01:32:59,397 --> 01:33:00,958
I already lost.

1474
01:33:01,118 --> 01:33:05,440
You just keep talking and talking
and talking. And you never listen.

1475
01:33:05,598 --> 01:33:08,360
You certainly don't know
what you're talking about.

1476
01:33:08,519 --> 01:33:10,964
- You just don't know what it's like.
- What what's like?

1477
01:33:11,120 --> 01:33:12,321
Alcatraz!

1478
01:33:13,440 --> 01:33:16,845
Where do you think they're gonna send me
those 10 years you're talking about?

1479
01:33:17,001 --> 01:33:19,042
They're gonna send me back to Alcatraz.

1480
01:33:19,201 --> 01:33:22,410
- Henri, when it's over, you'll be alive.
- I'm Henri.

1481
01:33:23,202 --> 01:33:26,084
I'm the one that's gotta do the time,
not you.

1482
01:33:26,242 --> 01:33:28,807
And I can't do it. I can't do it.

1483
01:33:28,963 --> 01:33:31,528
I can't, all right?

1484
01:33:32,203 --> 01:33:33,884
Listen, it's not worth it.

1485
01:33:34,404 --> 01:33:36,084
It's not worth it.

1486
01:33:36,404 --> 01:33:38,368
Nothing's worth going back there.

1487
01:33:38,525 --> 01:33:39,769
Mm-mm.

1488
01:33:41,765 --> 01:33:43,729
Sixty-seven thousand fans...

1489
01:33:43,886 --> 01:33:45,773
...at Municipal Stadium in Cleveland...

1490
01:33:45,926 --> 01:33:50,172
...watching to see if Joe DiMaggio can keep
his 56-game hitting streak alive.

1491
01:33:50,327 --> 01:33:54,453
Jim Bagby on the mound, works the count
to 1 and 1, runner on first base.

1492
01:33:54,608 --> 01:33:56,528
Here's the pitch. Joe DiMaggio swings.

1493
01:33:56,687 --> 01:33:59,012
It's a ground ball hit out to short
to Lou Boudreau.

1494
01:33:59,168 --> 01:34:02,616
He?ips it to Ray Mack for one out.
The relay to Grimes at first...

1495
01:34:02,769 --> 01:34:04,930
...it's in time for a double play.

1496
01:34:05,089 --> 01:34:08,178
Joe DiMaggio's 56-game hitting streak
is stopped.

1497
01:34:13,651 --> 01:34:16,259
Yeah?
- Mrs. Rosetta Dial?

1498
01:34:31,454 --> 01:34:32,895
Why are we in here, Jim?

1499
01:34:33,054 --> 01:34:36,340
Maybe there are some things
worth fighting for, Henri.

1500
01:34:42,656 --> 01:34:44,184
Henri?

1501
01:34:44,577 --> 01:34:46,421
Do I know you?

1502
01:34:47,577 --> 01:34:50,578
I'm- I'm Rosetta, Henri.

1503
01:34:52,258 --> 01:34:54,178
I'm your sister.

1504
01:34:57,459 --> 01:34:58,463
Um...

1505
01:35:00,540 --> 01:35:02,145
My, uh...

1506
01:35:02,860 --> 01:35:05,785
My baby's name is Henri.

1507
01:35:11,862 --> 01:35:13,422
You know, Mr. Stamphill says that-

1508
01:35:13,582 --> 01:35:16,267
I was...

1509
01:35:16,983 --> 01:35:18,992
...beginning to think...

1510
01:35:20,984 --> 01:35:23,385
...that you wasn't real. That I...

1511
01:35:24,185 --> 01:35:25,790
...made you up in my mind.

1512
01:35:29,065 --> 01:35:30,910
- I want you to come-
- Rosetta.

1513
01:35:32,426 --> 01:35:36,235
I want you to tell Jim that I appreciate
him bringing you down here...

1514
01:35:36,387 --> 01:35:40,032
...and knowing that you turned out okay.

1515
01:35:40,187 --> 01:35:44,476
That means a lot. I want you to tell him,
come Monday morning...

1516
01:35:45,068 --> 01:35:48,833
...he's gonna plead me guilty
just like I said.

1517
01:35:51,630 --> 01:35:55,995
I wish I wasn't so scared of them,
Rosetta.

1518
01:35:58,510 --> 01:36:00,672
I wish to God I wasn't.

1519
01:36:17,634 --> 01:36:19,796
You take care of yourself now.

1520
01:38:17,977 --> 01:38:20,859
You may call your
next witness, Mr. Stamphill.

1521
01:38:21,017 --> 01:38:22,937
Your Honor, be just a second.

1522
01:38:23,418 --> 01:38:24,422
I'm your friend.

1523
01:38:24,578 --> 01:38:27,023
On the outside,
I'd be lucky to consider you my friend.

1524
01:38:27,179 --> 01:38:28,980
Therefore, I'm not gonna kill you.

1525
01:38:29,139 --> 01:38:31,900
Are you going to call a witness
sometime today, counselor?

1526
01:38:32,060 --> 01:38:33,664
Yes, Your Honor.

1527
01:38:33,820 --> 01:38:37,268
If you wanna change your plea, you go up
there and do it. I'm not gonna do it.

1528
01:38:37,421 --> 01:38:39,582
- Plead me guilty.
- I don't think you are guilty.

1529
01:38:39,741 --> 01:38:41,389
- That doesn't matter.
- It does to me.

1530
01:38:41,542 --> 01:38:44,390
Okay, counselor, I am very close
to finding you in contempt of-

1531
01:38:44,542 --> 01:38:46,703
Your Honor, the defense calls
Mr. Henri Young.

1532
01:38:46,862 --> 01:38:48,106
No.

1533
01:38:48,263 --> 01:38:49,464
He just lost the case.

1534
01:38:49,623 --> 01:38:51,543
You wanna change your plea,
you go up there.

1535
01:38:51,704 --> 01:38:54,269
I repeat, I'm not gonna do it for you.

1536
01:38:55,944 --> 01:38:59,426
Counselor, unless-
He's coming, Your Honor.

1537
01:39:00,505 --> 01:39:01,630
Go ahead, tell them.

1538
01:39:10,507 --> 01:39:12,428
Tell them, not me.

1539
01:39:16,508 --> 01:39:19,313
- You better ask me the right questions.
- I'll ask what I want.

1540
01:39:19,468 --> 01:39:21,116
- And I'll answer what I want.
- Fine.

1541
01:39:21,269 --> 01:39:22,316
Fine.

1542
01:39:26,430 --> 01:39:29,835
Guilty, guilty, guilty.

1543
01:39:33,631 --> 01:39:36,872
Stand up. Put your hand on the Bible.

1544
01:39:39,472 --> 01:39:43,313
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth and nothing but the truth...

1545
01:39:43,473 --> 01:39:45,360
- ... so help you God?
- So help me God.

1546
01:39:45,513 --> 01:39:48,438
- State your name for the records.
- Henri Young. Henri Young.

1547
01:39:48,594 --> 01:39:50,155
Be seated.

1548
01:39:50,435 --> 01:39:51,439
Your Honor-

1549
01:39:51,594 --> 01:39:53,439
Wanna wait until I've asked a question?

1550
01:39:53,595 --> 01:39:55,637
- I haven't asked yet.
- He's trying to trick me.

1551
01:39:55,795 --> 01:39:59,277
Please instruct the witness to refrain
from speaking until I ask a question...

1552
01:39:59,436 --> 01:40:01,520
...and then just to answer
the question I ask.

1553
01:40:01,677 --> 01:40:04,122
- He's your witness, counselor.
- He won't listen to me.

1554
01:40:04,277 --> 01:40:07,039
- He trying to trick me. I just-
Silence, Mr. Young.

1555
01:40:07,838 --> 01:40:11,440
Now, here's the way it works.
Mr. Stamphill will ask you a question...

1556
01:40:11,598 --> 01:40:13,246
...and you may answer that question.

1557
01:40:13,398 --> 01:40:17,600
However, Mr. Stamphill cannot coerce you
into testifying against yourself.

1558
01:40:17,759 --> 01:40:19,364
Now, you do understand that?

1559
01:40:19,520 --> 01:40:20,644
Yeah, I just want to-

1560
01:40:20,800 --> 01:40:24,641
Did you and I have a conversation in which
you told me you wish to change your plea-?

1561
01:40:24,801 --> 01:40:30,170
Mr. Stamphill, you will wait until
I have finished instructing the witness.

1562
01:40:30,322 --> 01:40:32,646
That's okay.
That's the question I wanted him to ask.

1563
01:40:32,803 --> 01:40:34,931
It is not okay.

1564
01:40:35,083 --> 01:40:39,688
And I do not need you to tell me
what is or is not okay.

1565
01:40:40,284 --> 01:40:42,652
In this courtroom,
I am the one who decides...

1566
01:40:42,804 --> 01:40:45,686
...what is or is not okay.

1567
01:40:45,845 --> 01:40:47,450
Okay?

1568
01:40:47,645 --> 01:40:50,646
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Well, thank you very much.

1569
01:40:51,765 --> 01:40:54,330
Counselors, approach the bench.

1570
01:40:58,207 --> 01:41:00,695
Now, you wanna tell me
what the hell is going on here?

1571
01:41:00,847 --> 01:41:02,015
I'm just trying-

1572
01:41:02,168 --> 01:41:05,257
I mean, your own defendant
is looking to me to protect him from you.

1573
01:41:05,408 --> 01:41:06,456
So, what's going on?

1574
01:41:06,608 --> 01:41:08,889
I know, Your Honor,
it seems very strange but-

1575
01:41:09,049 --> 01:41:12,618
As far as I'm concerned, you're an idiot
to put him on the stand for any reason.

1576
01:41:12,769 --> 01:41:15,170
Asking your own client
to testify against himself.

1577
01:41:15,690 --> 01:41:19,260
It doesn't seem to make a lot of sense,
but the prosecution isn't objecting so-

1578
01:41:19,411 --> 01:41:21,016
No, I'm not. Let him continue.

1579
01:41:21,171 --> 01:41:22,459
Shut up.

1580
01:41:22,972 --> 01:41:24,980
- Stamphill-
- Enough damage has been done.

1581
01:41:25,132 --> 01:41:29,301
- I don't think I can mess things up any more.
- Yes, you can.

1582
01:41:29,493 --> 01:41:33,182
All right. All right.
But you're on a very short leash, Stamphill.

1583
01:41:33,333 --> 01:41:34,981
A very short leash.

1584
01:41:35,134 --> 01:41:37,895
I will throw you in jail
for contempt myself.

1585
01:41:38,895 --> 01:41:42,497
Now, let's get this goddamn show
on the road.

1586
01:41:45,416 --> 01:41:48,657
Don't let him rattle you, James.
I think you're doing a great job.

1587
01:41:50,336 --> 01:41:52,104
Mr. Young, stop playing with that.

1588
01:41:55,417 --> 01:41:59,903
Now, do you or do you not wish
to continue testifying, Mr. Young?

1589
01:42:00,059 --> 01:42:02,340
It's okay. He asked me the right question.

1590
01:42:03,139 --> 01:42:05,507
Counselor, you may proceed.

1591
01:42:08,220 --> 01:42:11,702
Mr. Young, did you and I not have
a conversation last Friday...

1592
01:42:11,861 --> 01:42:14,786
...which you told me
you wished to change your plea to guilty?

1593
01:42:15,262 --> 01:42:17,947
Yeah, yeah, yeah. That's...

1594
01:42:18,102 --> 01:42:20,830
I wanna change my plea.
That's what I told you.

1595
01:42:20,983 --> 01:42:24,344
I'm gonna ask you the single
most important question I can ask you.

1596
01:42:24,503 --> 01:42:26,303
It's what this whole trial is about.

1597
01:42:26,864 --> 01:42:29,068
Are you guilty of the murder
of Rufus McCain?

1598
01:42:29,224 --> 01:42:31,986
I wanna change my plea to guilty.
That's what I said.

1599
01:42:32,145 --> 01:42:35,310
I didn't ask what you said you wanted to do.
I asked if you are guilty.

1600
01:42:35,465 --> 01:42:37,789
Objection, Your Honor.
He's badgering the witness.

1601
01:42:37,945 --> 01:42:40,586
- He's my witness, for chrissakes.
- I'm not your nothing.

1602
01:42:40,746 --> 01:42:43,868
If the accused wants to enter
a plea of guilty, I don't know why-

1603
01:42:44,027 --> 01:42:48,349
Silence. Mr. Stamphill,
you are skating on very thin ice here.

1604
01:42:48,787 --> 01:42:51,909
Maybe, Your Honor,
but I'd like to get to the other side.

1605
01:42:53,588 --> 01:42:57,430
Very well. You may proceed,
at your own peril.

1606
01:42:57,589 --> 01:42:58,594
Thank you.

1607
01:43:02,230 --> 01:43:04,838
Let me take this one step at a time.

1608
01:43:05,551 --> 01:43:09,360
Mr. Young, we had a conversation
in which I told you...

1609
01:43:09,511 --> 01:43:12,797
...I felt with the way the trial was going,
the most you'd have to face...

1610
01:43:12,952 --> 01:43:16,313
...more than likely, would be
another 10 years. Maybe even less.

1611
01:43:16,472 --> 01:43:18,961
- You don't give a shit-
- Ten years, that's what I said.

1612
01:43:19,113 --> 01:43:20,161
Yeah, yeah, but-

1613
01:43:20,313 --> 01:43:22,878
And then did you say to me,
that you were Henri...

1614
01:43:23,035 --> 01:43:25,523
...you were the guy
who had to do the time, not me?

1615
01:43:25,674 --> 01:43:28,556
You were the one back in Alcatraz
to do those 10 years, right?

1616
01:43:28,715 --> 01:43:31,640
That's what I told you.
Why are you doing this to me?

1617
01:43:31,796 --> 01:43:35,485
Because, Mr. Young, if you change
your plea to guilty, they will execute you.

1618
01:43:35,637 --> 01:43:36,641
You will die.

1619
01:43:36,796 --> 01:43:37,877
So fucking what?

1620
01:43:38,037 --> 01:43:39,685
I'd rather die than go back there!

1621
01:43:52,400 --> 01:43:55,008
- What did you say, Mr. Young?
- I said...

1622
01:43:56,320 --> 01:43:59,965
I said I'd rather die than go back there.
Can't you understand that?

1623
01:44:00,482 --> 01:44:03,810
Why, Henri? Why do you want to die?

1624
01:44:04,081 --> 01:44:05,729
Because.

1625
01:44:07,083 --> 01:44:08,611
Because I'm...

1626
01:44:10,243 --> 01:44:12,130
I'm scared of them.

1627
01:44:12,404 --> 01:44:15,448
I'm scared to go back there. I'm scared.

1628
01:44:15,604 --> 01:44:17,372
I'm scared. I'm scared.

1629
01:44:17,524 --> 01:44:20,613
Objection. He's finished-
I haven't finished anything.

1630
01:44:21,206 --> 01:44:22,853
Henri, look at me.

1631
01:44:23,005 --> 01:44:25,450
Henri, look at me. Look at me.

1632
01:44:25,605 --> 01:44:29,054
You were right. You were right,
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

1633
01:44:29,206 --> 01:44:31,968
I'm just talking to you right now.
Not the judge or the jury.

1634
01:44:32,127 --> 01:44:34,015
If you wanna die, we'll back you up.

1635
01:44:34,167 --> 01:44:36,209
I swear to God,
I will fight these bastards...

1636
01:44:36,368 --> 01:44:38,409
...so they will never do this
to anyone again.

1637
01:44:38,568 --> 01:44:40,610
You are not gonna die for nothing.

1638
01:44:40,769 --> 01:44:43,093
The choice is yours, Henri.

1639
01:44:43,369 --> 01:44:44,449
What do you wanna do?

1640
01:44:50,411 --> 01:44:53,173
I wanna stop being afraid.

1641
01:45:00,332 --> 01:45:02,100
All right.

1642
01:45:35,019 --> 01:45:36,786
Henri Young...

1643
01:45:38,739 --> 01:45:41,380
...are you guilty of the murder
of Rufus McCain?

1644
01:46:01,864 --> 01:46:03,829
I was the weapon...

1645
01:46:04,664 --> 01:46:06,913
...but I ain't no killer.

1646
01:46:09,065 --> 01:46:11,106
They're the murderers.

1647
01:46:21,468 --> 01:46:24,709
Bailiff, you may remove the prisoner.

1648
01:46:25,628 --> 01:46:27,789
Escort the prisoner to the holding room.

1649
01:46:54,354 --> 01:46:55,914
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1650
01:46:56,075 --> 01:46:58,520
you have received your instructions.

1651
01:46:58,675 --> 01:47:02,320
You may find the defendant guilty
of involuntary manslaughter...

1652
01:47:02,475 --> 01:47:06,045
...which carries with it a maximum penalty
of three years...

1653
01:47:06,196 --> 01:47:08,641
...in which case the defendant
will be remanded...

1654
01:47:08,797 --> 01:47:12,005
...to the custody of the warden
of Alcatraz.

1655
01:47:12,157 --> 01:47:16,926
Or you may find the defendant guilty
of murder in the first degree.

1656
01:47:17,078 --> 01:47:19,359
Without a recommendation for mercy...

1657
01:47:19,519 --> 01:47:23,688
...that verdict will carry with it
a sentence of death.

1658
01:48:10,208 --> 01:48:12,369
This court is now in session.

1659
01:48:13,009 --> 01:48:16,611
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,
how do you find?

1660
01:48:16,929 --> 01:48:18,894
The defendant will rise.

1661
01:48:20,690 --> 01:48:21,770
We, the jury...

1662
01:48:21,931 --> 01:48:23,535
...find the defendant, Henri Young...

1663
01:48:23,691 --> 01:48:26,092
...not guilty of murder
in the first-degree...

1664
01:48:26,251 --> 01:48:27,856
...and guilty of involuntary manslaughter.

1665
01:48:29,131 --> 01:48:30,572
Order. Order.

1666
01:48:30,731 --> 01:48:31,736
Your Honor...

1667
01:48:31,892 --> 01:48:34,533
...we would like permission
to address the court, if possible.

1668
01:48:34,693 --> 01:48:35,981
Very well.

1669
01:48:36,133 --> 01:48:38,654
Your Honor,
we have this day signed a petition...

1670
01:48:38,814 --> 01:48:41,138
...which I would like to read to the court.

1671
01:48:41,454 --> 01:48:45,295
"We would like the following to be read
into the record of this proceeding.

1672
01:48:45,455 --> 01:48:49,056
Though we know it will have
no legal or binding effect...

1673
01:48:49,216 --> 01:48:52,140
...we'd hope that it will have
a moral effect.

1674
01:48:53,336 --> 01:48:56,305
We, the members of the jury,
recommend and request...

1675
01:48:56,457 --> 01:48:59,785
...an immediate investigation
by the proper federal authorities...

1676
01:48:59,938 --> 01:49:03,540
...of the federal penitentiary
known as Alcatraz.

1677
01:49:03,698 --> 01:49:07,824
We find this institution, its warden,
and associate warden...

1678
01:49:07,979 --> 01:49:09,704
...guilty of crimes against humanity. "

1679
01:49:12,179 --> 01:49:14,580
Thank you. The jury is dismissed.

1680
01:49:14,741 --> 01:49:16,508
This trial is concluded.

1681
01:49:16,661 --> 01:49:19,542
All rise. The defendant
is remanded to the warden of Alcatraz.

1682
01:49:20,821 --> 01:49:22,229
News from San Francisco.

1683
01:49:22,382 --> 01:49:23,986
The Young trial concludes.

1684
01:49:24,142 --> 01:49:26,587
The Rock will be investigated
as Young is vindicated...

1685
01:49:26,742 --> 01:49:29,787
...by a verdict
of involuntary manslaughter.

1686
01:49:29,943 --> 01:49:32,192
As I walked out of the courtroom that day...

1687
01:49:32,544 --> 01:49:36,233
...I did not fully realize how much
Henri and I had actually accomplished.

1688
01:49:36,384 --> 01:49:38,229
It all just happened so fast.

1689
01:49:38,384 --> 01:49:41,506
Henri, Henri, I'm gonna be up to see you
as often as I can.

1690
01:49:41,665 --> 01:49:44,514
And then you can bring
that Blanche back for a second shot, huh?

1691
01:49:44,665 --> 01:49:46,346
Yeah, I'll try. See what I can do.

1692
01:49:46,506 --> 01:49:47,707
No place like home.

1693
01:49:47,866 --> 01:49:49,951
Henri, it's not over.

1694
01:49:50,107 --> 01:49:53,108
It's not over. I'm gonna appeal
to have you moved to another prison.

1695
01:49:53,268 --> 01:49:56,356
I'm gonna file motions
to have your original case reopened.

1696
01:49:56,508 --> 01:49:59,029
Henri and Jim, together again, huh?

1697
01:49:59,189 --> 01:50:01,470
That's right.
Henri and Jim, together again.

1698
01:50:02,189 --> 01:50:04,830
- Henri and Jim, together again.
- Hey, Jim.

1699
01:50:04,989 --> 01:50:08,995
I won, didn't I?
I mean, I really did something.

1700
01:50:09,150 --> 01:50:10,230
I won.

1701
01:50:10,951 --> 01:50:13,035
That's right, Henri, you won.

1702
01:50:13,431 --> 01:50:17,316
Hey, Jim, how many games
was DiMaggio's hitting streak?

1703
01:50:17,472 --> 01:50:18,912
- Fifty-four?
- No.

1704
01:50:19,073 --> 01:50:20,437
No, I got you.

1705
01:50:20,593 --> 01:50:21,881
It was 56, wasn't it?

1706
01:50:22,033 --> 01:50:23,234
Yeah. Ha-ha-ha.

1707
01:50:26,233 --> 01:50:28,362
I'll see you soon, Henri.

1708
01:50:28,874 --> 01:50:30,762
Take care of yourself.

1709
01:50:47,077 --> 01:50:49,161
The definition of victory is:

1710
01:50:49,318 --> 01:50:52,123
"Success in any contest or struggle.

1711
01:50:52,959 --> 01:50:55,360
Engagement ending in triumph. "

1712
01:51:04,961 --> 01:51:08,409
That was to be the last time
I was to see Henri Young alive.

1713
01:51:09,201 --> 01:51:13,163
Before the court date was set for an appeal,
his body was found in a cell.

1714
01:51:13,923 --> 01:51:17,328
- He laid beneath a single word-

1715
01:51:18,243 --> 01:51:19,848
"Victory. "

1716
01:51:20,804 --> 01:51:23,849
Henri Young taught me
the meaning of the word.

1717
01:51:34,126 --> 01:51:37,651
He was the only man that I have known
who gave more than he asked.

1718
01:51:37,807 --> 01:51:40,492
All that he ever wanted was a friend.

1719
01:51:40,648 --> 01:51:44,532
And I will always remember him
as one of the best friends I have ever had.

1720
01:51:45,968 --> 01:51:51,730
Unlike many men that live much longer,
Henri Young did not die in vain.

1721
01:51:52,649 --> 01:51:55,138
In the end, he was not afraid.

1722
01:51:55,850 --> 01:51:58,699
He lived and he died in triumph.

1723
01:52:00,651 --> 01:52:02,900
If only we could all do that.

1724
01:52:11,694 --> 01:52:13,178
Welcome home.

1725
01:52:14,734 --> 01:52:16,698
I've missed you, Henri.

1726
01:52:21,815 --> 01:52:23,420
Mr. Glenn...

1727
01:52:24,896 --> 01:52:28,901
...you can beat me,
you can put me back in that hole...

1728
01:52:29,057 --> 01:52:30,421
...whatever you wanna do...

1729
01:52:31,537 --> 01:52:33,666
...it doesn't matter to me.

1730
01:52:35,057 --> 01:52:36,705
Action:

1731
01:52:37,138 --> 01:52:38,863
I won.

1732
01:52:39,458 --> 01:52:41,303
Reaction:

1733
01:52:41,499 --> 01:52:44,664
You can't ever take that away from me.

1734
01:52:58,662 --> 01:53:00,462
Take him to the hole.

1735
01:53:20,986 --> 01:53:25,112
Charles Dickens once said
that solitary confinement was inhumane.

1736
01:53:25,387 --> 01:53:28,508
Seven months later,
the Supreme Court agreed.

1737
01:53:28,667 --> 01:53:32,629
And as a result of the facts brought out
in the trial of The People v. Henri Young.

1738
01:53:32,788 --> 01:53:35,790
...the dungeons of Alcatraz
were closed forever.

1739
01:53:36,069 --> 01:53:39,834
Associate Warden Glenn was brought up
on charges of mistreatment.

1740
01:53:39,990 --> 01:53:44,116
He was found guilty. He would never work
in the penal system again.

1741
01:53:44,551 --> 01:53:47,192
I remained in private practice.

1742
01:53:47,351 --> 01:53:49,600
I also became a baseball fan.

1743
01:53:50,992 --> 01:53:52,760
You did it, Henri.

